<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,666,892]" pageId="5" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,281,666,692]" pageId="5" pageNumber="60">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
(Modified from 
<bibRefCitation author="Lowry" box="[477,756,666,692]" pageId="5" pageNumber="65" refString="Lowry, J. K. &amp; Berents, P. B. (1996) The Erichtonius Group, a New perspective on a old problem (Cruatcea: Amphipoda: Corophioidea). Records of Australian Museum, 48, 75 - 109." type="journal article" year="1996">
Lowry &amp; Berents, 
<number box="[696,756,666,692]" pageId="5" pageNumber="60" value="1996.0">1996</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) Antenna 
<number box="[877,892,666,692]" pageId="5" pageNumber="60" value="1.0">1</number>
, peduncle article 
<number box="[1098,1113,666,692]" pageId="5" pageNumber="60" value="1.0">1</number>
produced dorsodistally and medially, partially overlapping article 
<number box="[602,619,706,732]" pageId="5" pageNumber="60" value="2.0">2</number>
. Outer plate of Maxilla 
<number box="[903,918,706,732]" pageId="5" pageNumber="60" value="1.0">1</number>
with 
<number box="[985,1044,706,732]" pageId="5" pageNumber="60" value="7.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="5.0">5–10</number>
setal teeth. Gnathopod 
<number box="[1324,1339,706,732]" pageId="5" pageNumber="60" value="2.0">2</number>
of male adult carpochelate and in female subchelate. Pereopods 
<number box="[809,869,746,772]" pageId="5" pageNumber="60" value="5.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="3.0">3 – 7</number>
dactyli all directed posteriorly. Pereopod 
<number box="[1361,1376,746,772]" pageId="5" pageNumber="60" value="7.0">7</number>
with 
<number box="[151,195,786,812]" pageId="5" pageNumber="60" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
small accessory spines. Pleopod 
<number box="[598,612,786,812]" pageId="5" pageNumber="60" value="2.0">2</number>
inner ramus reduced, 
<number box="[883,892,786,812]" pageId="5" pageNumber="60" value="1.0">1</number>
-articulate or pleopod unirramous. Pleopod 
<number box="[1421,1436,786,812]" pageId="5" pageNumber="60" value="3.0">3</number>
one reduced 
<number box="[307,316,826,852]" pageId="5" pageNumber="60" value="1.0">1</number>
-articulate ramus or pleopod absent. Uropod 
<number box="[865,880,826,852]" pageId="5" pageNumber="60" value="2.0">2</number>
with one ramus. Uropod 
<number box="[1196,1211,826,852]" pageId="5" pageNumber="60" value="3.0">3</number>
with one vestigial ramus bearing small recurved spines.
</paragraph>
